  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Curvature of a plane curve:
        <me>
          \kappa=\abs{\dv{\phi}{s}}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Derivation:
        <me>
          \tan\phi=\dv{y}{x}=\frac{\dd{y}/\dd{t}}{\dd{x}/\dd{t}}=\frac{y'}{x'}
        </me>
        <me>
          \dv{t}\tan\phi=\sec^{2}\phi \dv{\phi}{t}=\dfrac{x'y''-y'x''}{(x')^2}
        </me>
        <me>
          \dv{\phi}{t}=\dfrac{x'y''-y'x''}{(x')^2}\cdot\dfrac{1}{1+\tan^2\phi}=\frac{x'y''-y'x''}{(x')^{2}+(y')^{2}}
        </me>
        <me>
          \dv{\phi}{s}=\dfrac{\dd\phi/\dd{t}}{\dd s/\dd{t}}=\dfrac{x'y''-y'x''}{((x')^2+(y')^2)^{3/2}}
        </me>
        <me>
          \kappa=\dfrac{|x'y''-y'x''|}{((x')^2+(y')^2)^{3/2}}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Radius of curvature is <m>1/\kappa</m>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Center of curvature is the limit of where normal lines intersect
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
